# Partially Normalize Operational Tables

The objective is to reduce data duplication in operational tables by removing denormalized names and snapshot fields that can easily be retrieved via joins, keeping the tables lightweight.

## User Review Required
> [!WARNING]
> This requires a database migration that will **DROP** columns from live tables. This is an irreversible structural change. Please ensure no external queries depend on these columns before applying this plan.

## Proposed Changes

### Database Migration
A new migration (`drizzle/0010_normalize_tables.sql`) will be created to drop the specified columns:
- `faculty_subject_assignments`: DROP `faculty_name`, `subject_name`, `division_name`, `course_code`
- `counselor_division_assignments`: DROP `faculty_name`, `division_name`
- `timetable_entries`: DROP `subject_name`, `faculty_name`, `division_name`, `course_code`
- `attendance_sessions`: DROP `subject_name`, `faculty_name`, `division_name`
- `student_enrollment_history`: DROP `academic_year_id`, `semester_no`, `division_name`

### Schema Updates

#### [MODIFY] schema.ts
- Remove the dropped columns from `facultySubjectAssignments`, `counselorDivisionAssignments`, `timetableEntries`, `attendanceSessions`, and `studentEnrollmentHistory`.
- Update typescript definitions.

### API Route Updates

#### facultySubjectAssignments
- **[MODIFY] app/api/admin/timetable/route.ts**: Fetch `subjectName`, `facultyName`, `courseCode` via joins or omit them.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/admin/subject-assignments/route.ts**: Join with `faculty`, `subjects`, and `divisions` to return the names to the frontend.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/internal-exams/assignments/route.ts**: Add joins.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/internal-exams/marks/route.ts**: Add joins to get names.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/internal-evaluation/route.ts**: Add joins.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/internal-evaluation/export/route.ts**: Add joins.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/internal-evaluation/finalize/route.ts**: Add joins.

#### counselorDivisionAssignments
- **[MODIFY] app/api/admin/assignments/route.ts**: Fetch `divisionName` via join.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/auth/login/route.ts**: Fetch `divisionName` via join.
- **[MODIFY] app/api/counselor/divisions/[id]/students/route.ts**: No change needed if names aren't selected from assignment.

#### timetableEntries & attendanceSessions
- **[MODIFY] app/api/attendance/sessions/route.ts**: Join with `timetableEntries` -> `facultySubjectAssignments` -> `subjects` & `faculty` to get `subjectName` and `facultyName`.
